Package: hidrobR
Type: Package
Title: Functions to download hidrological data from conventional and telemetric gauges from National Water Agency.
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Marcos Roberto Benso
Maintainer: Marcos Roberto Benso <marcosbenso@gmail.com>
Description: This package is aimed to help students and researchers to develop hydrological analysis and modeling
              in Brazilian catchments using data from conventional and telemetric gauges from the Brazilian National Water Agency.
              The functions help to download and visualize hydrological data in R.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
Depends: 
    R (>= 2.10), dplyr, xml2, tidyr, httr, lubridate, XML, RJSONIO, jsonlite
Imports: dplyr, xml2, tidyr, httr, lubridate, XML, RJSONIO, jsonlite
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),dplyr, xml2, tidyr, httr, lubridate, XML, RJSONIO, jsonlite
Config/testthat/edition: 3
